          <!-- THE NEW PORK TIMES — News Feed -->
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>[ NEWSFEED.EXE — The New Pork Times ]</h3>
            <div class="news-layout">
              <div class="news-main">

                <!-- PORK NEWS NETWORK -->
                <div class="news-outlet">
                  <div class="outlet-header pnn">
                    <span class="outlet-logo">PNN</span>
                    <span class="outlet-name">Pork News Network</span>
                    <span class="outlet-tag">BREAKING</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="news-article">
                    <h4 class="news-headline">BREAKING: Local Pig Registers 10,000th Domain, Says "I Can Stop Whenever I Want"</h4>
                    <p class="news-byline">By Snout McTrotter | 2 hours ago</p>
                    <p class="news-body">A local pig was seen registering yet another .com domain at 3 AM, bringing their total to an estimated 10,000 domains. "It's not an addiction," the pig insisted while browsing available .io names. "Porkbun just makes it too easy and too cheap. This is their fault, really." Friends and family staged an intervention, but were distracted when they learned .dev domains were on sale.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="news-article">
                    <h4 class="news-headline">DNS Propagation Delays Blamed on Mercury Being in Retrograde</h4>
                    <p class="news-byline">By Hamlet O'Brien | 5 hours ago</p>
                    <p class="news-body">Internet astrologers confirm what sysadmins have long suspected: DNS propagation times are directly correlated with planetary alignment. "When Mercury is in retrograde, nameservers just vibe differently," explained one horoscope-certified network engineer.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <!-- PORK-TACU -->
                <div class="news-outlet">
                  <div class="outlet-header porktacu">
                    <span class="outlet-logo">P!</span>
                    <span class="outlet-name">Pork-tacu</span>
                    <span class="outlet-tag">GAMING + TECH</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="news-article">
                    <h4 class="news-headline">Review: Pork-OS v1.0 Might Be the Best Operating System Nobody Asked For</h4>
                    <p class="news-byline">By GamerPig42 | 1 hour ago</p>
                    <p class="news-body">In a world dominated by Windows and macOS, a scrappy upstart pig-themed OS has entered the chat. "It boots with oinks, the file system is organized by farm sections, and the default wallpaper is a sunset over a domain registration page," our reviewer notes. "10/10 — it has a little something for everyone." We're giving it the coveted Pork-tacu Editor's Choice award.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="news-article">
                    <h4 class="news-headline">Top 10 Domain Names That Sound Like Video Game Bosses</h4>
                    <p class="news-byline">By XxPorkSlayerxX | 3 hours ago</p>
                    <p class="news-body">#1: darkfiredragon.gg, #2: ultimatevoid.io, #3: shadowbane.dev — "These domains go HARD," writes our listicle expert. "Imagine getting an email from someone@chaosblade.gg. That person has definitely beaten Elden Ring at level 1. Register yours on Porkbun before someone else claims your ultimate gamer identity."</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <!-- PGN — Pork Gaming Network -->
                <div class="news-outlet">
                  <div class="outlet-header pgn">
                    <span class="outlet-logo">PGN</span>
                    <span class="outlet-name">Pork Gaming Network</span>
                    <span class="outlet-tag">ESPORTS</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="news-article">
                    <h4 class="news-headline">Porkbun Pig Speedruns Domain Registration in 47 Seconds, New World Record</h4>
                    <p class="news-byline">By SpeedPork_TAS | 45 min ago</p>
                    <p class="news-body">In a stunning display of oink-hand coordination, the Porkbun Pig registered a new .com domain in just 47 seconds — from homepage to checkout confirmation. "The key is pre-loading your payment info and having your domain name ready," the pig explained during their post-run analysis on PorkTube. Skeptics claim the run used tool-assisted snout (TAS), but the pig insists it was all natural talent and low, low Porkbun prices.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="news-article">
                    <h4 class="news-headline">Competitive Domain Squatting Now Recognized as Official Esport</h4>
                    <p class="news-byline">By ProOinker2026 | 2 hours ago</p>
                    <p class="news-body">The International Domain Athletics Federation (IDAF) has officially recognized competitive domain registration as an esport. Teams of 5 will compete to register the most creative domains in a 10-minute window. Porkbun has been named the official registrar sponsor. "We've been training for this our entire lives," said Team Snout's captain.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

              </div>

              <!-- SIDEBAR TICKER -->
